                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="15114827" author="rohini" created="Mon, 25 Jan 2016 06:34:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;  Had another user reported issue where user had cross + scalar from same Split. The script was actually wrong as it was using . instead of :: operator.  But since both inputs had 1 record, the script worked producing the right results. it The script failed to run in Tez with &quot;java.lang.IllegalArgumentException: bound must be positive&quot;  as parallelism of the cross vertex was set to 0.  Main problem was not parallelism estimation,  but the planning where the shuffle vertex for Cross was overwritten with the broadcast vertex for scalar.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Multi-query planning should differentiate between POPackage inputs and non-POPackage inputs. Splittee should be merged if it has either POPackage or a non-POPackage input and not both.  &lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="15141406" author="rohini" created="Wed, 10 Feb 2016 18:33:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed to trunk a week back. Just closing now. +1 is in review board - &lt;a href=&quot;https://reviews.apache.org/r/42709/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://reviews.apache.org/r/42709/&lt;/a&gt;. Thanks for the review Daniel.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
